         <abstract>
            <p>When a local minimum of a function of several variables has been found by us of an algorithm for finding such minima numerically, one often runs the same algorithm many times with different starting values in the hopes of finding a lower minimum. Here, under the assumption that a local minimum is known, a process with analytical criteria is described which sometimes finds smaller local minima in an algorithmic manner.</p>
          </abstract>
